Head (
Fig. 21
) mostly pale yellow. Face pale yellow at base, with brown groove near ventral margin and brown on margin; parafacial pale yellow except blackish brown inner margin, with narrow brown median stripe on basal 1/2 and an elliptical brown ventroapical spot. Frons wider than long slightly, trapeziform (anterior margin shorter than posterior margin), with pair of narrow brownish median stripes, extending to ocellar triangle from anterior margin; ocellar triangle blackish gray, ocellar seta developed, longer than anterior fronto-orbital seta, anterior frontoorbital seta shorter than posterior fronto-orbital seta; fronto-orbital seta each with 1 blackish brown basal spot fused to a narrow stripe. Gena about 1/5 height of eye. Occiput with grayish pruinosity. Antenna yellow, flagellomere 1 and arista broken. Brown spot present between eye and antenna. Proboscis pale brownish yellow, with yellowish and blackish setulae; palpus brown with black setulae.

Abdomen (
Fig. 25
) blackish brown, with blackish gray pruinosity, but syntergosternite and epandrium yellow. Male genitalia (
Figs. 26–30
): syntergosternite slender, circular with pair of small triangular ventral processes in anterior view, almost confluent with epandrium; epandrium with several rows of dorsal setae, each with brownish spot at base; surstylus consisting of 1 anterior process and 1 posteroapical process in lateral view; anterior process long with setae, apex acute, posterior process short, widening apically and truncated; hypandrium small, Y-shaped, inner process almost membranaceous. Gonopod long and strong, curved in ventral view, with long setulae and roughness at tip, curved apically in lateral view; phallus consisting of 1 ventral sclerite and 1 dorsal sclerite, dumbbell-shaped in lateral view; phallus with small apical concavity in ventral view. Phallapodeme long, slightly shorter than phallus.
